24. Magn Reson Imaging Clin N Am. 2018 May;26(2):179-190. doi:10.1016/j.mric.2017.12.001. Epub 2018 Feb 1.Breast MR Imaging: Atlas of Anatomy, Physiology, Pathophysiology, and BreastImaging Reporting and Data Systems Lexicon.Martaindale SR(1).Author information: (1)Department of Diagnostic Radiology, Breast Imaging Section, The University of Texas MD Anderson Cancer Center, 1515 Holcombe Boulevard, Unit 1350, Houston, TX 77030, USA. Electronic address: smartaindale@mdanderson.org.The latest edition of the Breast Imaging Reporting and Data Systems lexicon,copyrighted in 2013, contains several changes to the breast MR imaging section.Most changes were implemented to standardize descriptors across breast imagingmodalities. New sections on special topics and implant evaluation are included.We review basic MR imaging breast anatomy and a detailed pictorial review of the Breast Imaging Reporting and Data Systems lexicon, including these new sections. In each section we discuss which descriptors are more concerning for malignancyand information radiologists can use to better categorize findings as lower risk or benign.Copyright Â© 2017 Elsevier Inc. All rights reserved.DOI: 10.1016/j.mric.2017.12.001 PMID: 29622124 